name: nytimes

name: nytimes
text:
Mahdia Chowdhury returned from her Ivy League dorm to her family’s home in Queens. She started making life-or-death decisions for her father, a cab driver who had sacrificed everything for her.

Day and night, ambulances howled outside their door. https://t.co/f7v5Bc7Wrq https://t.co/y5Kn1VpSAe

name: nytimes
text:
Elmhurst Hospital was flooded by coronavirus patients, with doctors overworked and a refrigerated truck posted outside to hold the dead.

One doctor called it apocalyptic. A single day brought 13 deaths, which the local rumor mill spun into 15; 25; 1,000. https://t.co/f7v5Bc7Wrq https://t.co/PbfV4IMcQF

name: nytimes
text:
The worst passed. There was a summer-time drop in virus cases. The residents of Queens got a brief reprieve. 

But as the city and country battle a resurgence of the virus, the worry is whether the lessons of the hellish spring will be remembered. https://t.co/f7v5Bc7Wrq
